Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

No_show is a situation in which a patient did not show up for an appointment initially scheduled with the doctor. This means that valuable time could be lost waiting for the patient to show up. Therefore, it will be helpful to have some insight into the reason why this happen and to be able to reduce their occurence.

The data set that was used for this analysis was obtained from kaggle site and was downloaded from here. This dataset contain information about over 100,000 medical appointments in different hospitals across Brazil.

The data set contains the following columns:

1 The patientID: This is a unique identifier for each of the patients this column will be dropped during the analysis because we desire to find general patterns within the population

2 The AppointmentID: This is the unique identifier for each appointment. This column will also be dropped because

3 Gender: The patient in our data set were identified as either male or female. This will be an indicator to consider if male or female tend to keep their appointments

4 ScheduledDay and the AppointmentDay: This describe the day the patient schedule the meeting and the day the appointment was scheduled. we will engineer several other features from this two column that will enable us determine the waiting time and the weekday as we try to uncover various indicators for noshow appointment.

5 Age: Age has always been identified as a factor associated with predisposition to certain types of disease and it will be a factor to consider with respect to whether an individual will show up or not. also we will love to know which age group have a higher ratio of showing up for appointment

6 Neighborhood: This shows the location of the hospital. We will be able to consider the prevalence of noshow appointment by locality.

7 Scholarship: This column name will be changed to 'sponsorship' to better reflect the implication as it describes those patient enrolled into Brasilian social welfare program Bolsa Familia. those enrolled are recoreded as 1 while those not enrolled are recorded as o

8 Hipertension, Diabetes, Alcoholism: These are particular ailments of patients collected in the dataset. we will be analysing to uncover patterns on tendency to show up or not for their appointments. patient with this ailment are recorded with a 1 and those without the ailment are recorded with a 0 for their respective column.

9 Handcap There are five unique variable in this column describing whether a patient has any physical disability and the types are tagged 1,2,3,or 4. If a person does not have a diability it is recorded as 0.

10 SMS_recieved:Getting a reminder can sometimes be helpful in ensuring that the scheduled appointment was honored. it will be interesting to see how effective is this strategy in improving the numbers of appointment kept.

11 No_show: This is our target variable and we will be answering many question from the analysis, to discover patterns across the other feature variables that influence the outcome of this variable. The column has been coded as Yes or No Yes: indicating that a patient did not show up and No: indicating that a patient showed up for the appointment.

For clearity, we will substitute this column with a more descriptive column, status which will have two values, show and no_show. show indicates that the patient showed up no_show indicates that the patient did not show up.

Question(s) for Analysis¶

the focus of this analysis is to answer the question. What are the features that best describes patient that showed up for their appointment amongst the features available in the dataset? we will consider this question from different perspectives like, the Age and Gender of the patient, the time factors like the waiting time and the day of the week of the appointment, the type of ailment, the handicap status and the type of disability, the enrolment status in the national welfare program, the status of SMS_recieved as well as the locality of the hospital.

    Exploratory Data Analysis¶

    In this section, the cleaned Data set will be explored with the aim of answering this question. What are the features that best describes patient that showed up for their appointment amongst the features available in the dataset .

    To help us answer this question,we will consider the following factors:

  • Which of the Genders Keep their appointment the more ?
  • Is age a strong indicator for whether an individual show up or not ?
  • Considering both age and gender, how does these relate with the appointment status?
  • Is waiting time an indicator for whether an individual show up or not?
  • Is the appointment week-day an indicator for whether an individual show up or not ?
  • Is there any relationship between the type of ailment and the appointment status ?
  • Is there any relationship between the Handicap type and the appointment status ?
  • Is there any relationship between the sponsorship status and the appointment status ?
  • How does scholarship and Handicap status affect the appointment status ?
  • Is there any relationship between the sms reminder and the appointment status?

    def unpacker (list_1,list_2,list_3):
    """
    unpacks a list into two lists based on their position in the list
    The first list contains all elements with even index
    The second list contains all elements with odd index.
    
    Args:
    arg_1(list): The list to be unpacked
    arg_2(list): The empty list to unpack all elements with even index
    arg_3(list): The empty list to unpack all elements with odd index
    
    
    Returns:
    list_1
    list_2
    """
    for a,x in enumerate(list_1):
      if a % 2 == 0:
       list_2.append(x)
      else:
       list_3.append(x)
    return list_2, list_3

    # defining a function, double_stacked barchart
def double_stacked_barchart(df_01):
    '''
    Plots a double stacked barchart using the the four columns in the dataframe
    
    args:
    args_1(DataFrame): The dataframe to plot from
    
    Returns:
    bar_1: The first bar from first column
    bar_2: The second bar from third column
    bar_3: The third bar from second column
    bar_4: The fourth bar from fourth column
    loc: The x_ticks locations
    
    '''
    #unpack the relevant series objects from th df
    index= df_01.index
    series_1=df_01.iloc[:,0]
    series_2=df_01.iloc[:,2]
    series_3=df_01.iloc[:,1]
    series_4=df_01.iloc[:,3]
    #The x location
    
    ind=np.arange(len(index))
    width=0.35
    # creating a plot to show the status by age and gender
    fig,ax=plt.subplots()
    bar_1= ax.bar(ind, series_1,width,color='#1f77b4')
    bar_2=ax.bar(ind, series_2,width, bottom=series_1,color='#ff7f0e')
    bar_3=ax.bar(ind+width, series_3,width,color='#144c73')
    bar_4=ax.bar(ind+width, series_4,width, bottom=series_3,color='#8e4200')
    loc=ind+width/2
   

    return (bar_1,bar_2,bar_3,bar_4,loc)

    • Conclusions¶

    In this analysis our focus has been on discovering factors that best describe the show or no_show condition of the appointment status. In exploring the dataset, the following conclusion can be reached.

  • Gender is not a strong indicator as the difference in show rate between the two gender is less than 1%.The show rate for male is slightly higher at 80% while that of the female is at 79.7%

  • Age is a stronger indicator of no_show as the rate of no_show is low for children within the age group of 0-2 at 17.5% then increases continously until it peaks at the teenage group 14-18 at 25%. Then continues to reduce for adults before reaching its minimum for age group between 65-78 at 15% and then start to increase and peaks at age group 99-115 at 27%.

  • This describes the dire need for health care for babies under the age of 2 and the increased conciousness towards healthy living as one become adult. Also, the tendency for the aged ones between the ages 79 to 115 to need the help of others to help maintain their health.

  • The waiting time is another strong indicator. It can be observed that the general trend is that, the more the waiting time the more the rate of No_show. This is not a linear relationship but it is easy to spot that the lowest no_show rate is for waiting_period less than 20 days at 17% this is more than doubled for waiting period of up to 160 days at 45%

  • When considering the waiting _periods within 20 days, we can see a steady increase in no_show rate as the waiting _period increases.

  • The ailment type is flat. Although, the rate of no show is highest among the alcoholism group at 20%, this is not much different from the diabetes and hypertension group at 18% and 17% respectively

  • The handicap type is a strong indicator of the show rate we can see that handicap type 1 has the lowest no show rate at 17.8%, this increases steadily across the handicap type 2 and 3 peaking at 33% for handicap type 4

  • It can also be observed that sponsorship(i.e enrollment status into the Bolsa Familia welfare program) has a strong effect on the no_show rate across the different handicap type group particularly for the type 2 Handicap group where there is 5.5% no show rate with sponsorship and 21.8% no_show rate without sponsorship.

    Limitations¶

  • A major limitation is the lack of sufficient data especially for older age groups like age group between 98-115. It is likely that their low representation in the data set is a true representation of the larger population,but this will need to be investigated further.

  • Another limitation is that the data set has focused mostly on ailments that are more prevalent among adult group between the ages 19 and 78.Therefore, limiting the scope of this analysis and also making it difficult to determine how this analysis may have been biased towards these age groups
